    rectoEn: 'Fallen angel, rising star: definitions — and why the fall is not symmetric to the climb?',
    versoEn: 'FALLEN ANGEL: an investment-grade issuer downgraded to high yield — it crosses the frontier downward. RISING STAR: the reverse journey. The asymmetry: the fall triggers MECHANICAL sales — "IG only" mandates must sell, no opinion involved — simultaneous, into an HY pool several times smaller: the spread widens beyond the risk, a DISLOCATION premium. The climb forces nobody to buy. The anchor: Ford, March 2020 — $36bn switched at once, the largest fallen angel in history; back to IG in 2023.',
