    rectoEn: 'The CDS: the contract, the two legs, the liquid point?',
    versoEn: 'An over-the-counter contract between a protection BUYER and a protection SELLER, referenced on a REFERENCE ENTITY. Fixed leg: the buyer pays notional × spread/10,000 per year — in quarterly instalments on March 20, June 20, September 20 and December 20 — as long as the entity survives. Contingent leg: at default, the seller pays notional × (1 − R) and the premiums stop, pro rata. The market\'s liquid point: 5 years. The anchor: invented in 1994 by a JPMorgan team — credit risk detached from the paper that carries it, tradable in itself.',
