    rectoEn: 'The waterfall and the OC/IC tests: how the flows come down?',
    versoEn: 'Every quarter, the pool\'s flows — interest, then principal — descend the waterfall: SENIOR served first, then mezzanine, the equity collects what remains. Coverage tests stand guard: OC (collateral value / tranche notional) and IC (interest received / interest due) — below their thresholds, the waterfall is RE-ROUTED: flows meant for the lower tranches are diverted to repay the senior early. The anchor: subordination is a PAYMENT order, not only a loss order — the senior also protects itself by sucking up the flows as soon as the pool coughs.',
