    rectoEn: 'Mental math: 3-6% mezzanine, pool losses at 5% — the tranche\'s loss?',
    versoEn: 'Method: (L − A)/(D − A) = (5 − 3)/(6 − 3) = 2/3 = 66.666667% of ITS notional — while an untranched pool investor loses only 5%. Boundary checks: intact at L = 3% (the attachment), wiped out at L = 6% (the detachment). The anchor: the reference value of calculs.ts — and the sentence that goes with it: the pool lost 5%, the tranche two thirds; that is the cliff.',
